result.execSummary:
All charges against Zackary A. Partridge in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Zackary A. Partridge is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Case called @ 1:36 PM Defendant Zackary A. Partridge appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Matthew R. Leusink in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Emma K Blankschein appeared by video for Zackary A. Partridge. Defendant failed to appear for an Arraignment on March 22, 2022. Statement by ADA Ryan regarding the information that was not filed within 30 days of the bind over.  The Court enters a non prejudicial dismissal based on the lack of jurisdiction due to the failure of the information being filed within 30 days of the bind over of the defedant. The Court orders the $2000 Cash bond that was ordered forfeited on March 22, 2022 be returned to the defendant based on the lack of jurisdiction as of March 11, 2022.
Letter to Court Requesting Hearing & Warrant Cancellation

Case called @ 11:41 AM Defendant Zackary A. Partridge not in court.  Attorney Matthew R. Leusink in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Emma K Blankschein in court for Zackary A. Partridge. Based on non appearance the Court authorizes the issuance of a warrant extraditable within the Continental US. The Court orders the $2000 Cash Bond forfeited. 22TR94 & 22TR95 - Default Judgment entered. Court orders the bond amount noted on each citation w/ 60 DTP or PP.

22CF8, 22TR94 & 22TR95. 10:31 AM Defendant Zackary A. Partridge appeared in court, Attorney Emma K Blankschein appeared in court for Zackary A. Partridge, Attorney Wes Kottke appeared in court for State of Wisconsin.  Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and potential punishment.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Preliminary Hearing and Time Limits discussed. Defendant wishes to waive preliminary hearing. Court questions defendant and accepts waiver of preliminary hearing. Court has read the complaint, finds probable cause and enters an order binding the defendant over. Attorney Blankschein requests arraignment to be set in a couple of weeks. ARGN Scheduled - NOH Given.
Arraignment scheduled for March 22, 2022 at 11:30 am.
